Hi everyone,
I wanted to migrate the web traffic HubSpot analytics data into the SQL server. So have tried using the Analytics API but got a permission error. (Should have the enterprise account access).
Also tried to fetch the HubSpot analytics data using OAuth connection but couldn't do it.
Is there any other way we can fetch the HubSpot analytics data except the manual export option?.
 
Can we able to integrate the HubSpot analytics data into google analytics and then migrate it to SQL server?.
 
Looking for some suggestions or help on this issue.
Will be glad if anyone has done this before or any suggestions are welcome.

Hey everyone I’ve noticed a trend here. If your question is NOT about the community built developer chrome browser extension. This is not the place you likely want to ask your questions, it wont be seen here by folks who know the answers.

Our channels are labeled based on their topics. If you have API questions, ask them in <#C2YHAHB6K|api> if you have local development questions, we have a <#CLJJXGTC0|local-development> channel. For questions on CRM extensions go to <#C2YHAHB6K|api>.If you have questions about <#CFPRTEGTX|modules> <#CSFGKSHT7|themes> <#C011F74BKQW|serverless-functions> <#CF540P856|seo> <#CJ5DN6RKP|email-development> <#CDU990ECW|drag-n-drop-pages> we have channels for those. If you want to suggest a feature addition/change post your idea to the community ideas forum so it can get upvotes - then cross post it to <#C26E7JT8V|ideas> just to give it visibility with fellow devs.
